## How to Use

### Step 1 — Organise training data
```
datasets/images/
  train/
    warrior_one/    ← your training JPEG images here
    tree_pose/
  test/
    warrior_one/    ← different images for testing
    tree_pose/
```

### Step 2 — Extract keypoints
```powershell
python scripts/preprocess.py
```
Outputs: `train_data.csv`, `test_data.csv`

### Step 3 — Train the classifier
```powershell
python scripts/train.py
```
Outputs: `exported_models/pose_classifier.keras`, `exported_models/class_names.json`

### Step 4 — Start the server
```powershell
uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```

### Step 5 — Test REST endpoint
```powershell
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/pose/classify -F "image=@your_pose.jpg"
```

### Step 6 — Connect frontend via WebSocket
```
ws://localhost:8000/pose/stream

Client sends:  JPEG bytes
Server replies: JSON PoseFrameResponse per frame
```

---

## Frontend Integration Guide

```js
// 1. Connect
const ws = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8000/pose/stream');

// 2. Capture & send frames at ~15-30fps
function sendFrame() {
  canvas.toBlob(blob => ws.send(blob), 'image/jpeg', 0.8);
  requestAnimationFrame(sendFrame);
}

// 3. Draw overlay from server response
ws.onmessage = (e) => {
  const data = JSON.parse(e.data);
  drawSkeleton(data.keypoints);       // connect the 17 dots
  showPoseBadge(data.pose_class, data.confidence);
  showFeedback(data.feedback);        // e.g. "Bend left knee 22° more"
};
```

### Sample JSON Response
```json
{
  "keypoints": [
    { "body_part": "LEFT_KNEE", "x": 312, "y": 480, "score": 0.93 },
    ...
  ],
  "pose_class": "warrior_one",
  "confidence": 0.87,
  "angles": { "left_knee": 68.4, "right_hip": 172.1 },
  "feedback": [
    {
      "joint": "left_knee",
      "current_angle": 68.4,
      "target_angle": 90.0,
      "delta": 21.6,
      "feedback": "Adjust your left knee by 22° more"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Adding More Poses

1. Add images to `datasets/images/train/<pose_name>/` and `test/<pose_name>/`
2. Run [scripts/preprocess.py](file:///d:/Python_Projects/yoga-backend/scripts/preprocess.py) → [scripts/train.py](file:///d:/Python_Projects/yoga-backend/scripts/train.py) again
3. Add reference angles for the new pose in [app/data/pose_references.json](file:///d:/Python_Projects/yoga-backend/app/data/pose_references.json)
